# --- Local dev (npm run dev) ---
# Browser calls http://localhost:5180/api/... and Vite proxies to the backend.
# Default proxy target is http://127.0.0.1:5000 (Coolgix backend default PORT).
# Uncomment and change if your API runs elsewhere:
# VITE_DEV_PROXY_TARGET=http://127.0.0.1:5000

# To skip the proxy and call the API directly from the browser in dev (needs CORS):
# VITE_DEV_USE_REMOTE_API=http://127.0.0.1:5000

# VITE_API_URL is NOT used in dev anymore (avoids wrong-port mistakes).
# Remove old lines like VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3000 — they are ignored.

# --- Production build (npm run build) ---
# Set the public API origin (no trailing slash), e.g.:
# VITE_API_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com
